==English==

===Etymology===
From French ''polythéisme'' (ca. 1580), English from the early 17th century,
a learned formation from [[poly-]] ({{term|πολύς|tr=polús||many|sc=polytonic}}) and -[[theism]] ({{term|θεός|tr=theós||god|sc=polytonic}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pɒliˈθiˈĭzˈəm}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The belief of the existence of many [[god]]s.

